Attorney general orders some asylum seekers to be held without bail The decision comes as the administration cracks down on asylum seekers.
The decision, which doesn't go into effect for 90 days, orders immigration judges to deny some asylum seekers from posting bail.
Attorney General William Barr leaves his home in McLean, Va., April 15, 2019.
Our Constitution does not allow the government to lock up asylum seekers without basic due process.
In May 2018, then-Attorney General Jeff Sessions enacted a zero-tolerance policy which lead to the separation of families along the border.